column8: Angry Birds is a video game franchise inspired primarily by a sketch of stylized wingless birds; with two billion downloads across all platforms. Angry Birds has been praised for its successful combination of addictive gameplay; comical style; and low price.)

The Space Needle is an observation tower in Seattle; Washington. Six parachutists have leaped from the tower since its opening; but this activity is only legal with prior consent. Four jumpers were part of various promotions; and the other two were arrested.)

The Walt Disney Company; commonly known as Disney; is an American diversified multinational mass media corporation headquartered at the Walt Disney Studios in Burbank; California. It is the world second largest broadcasting and cable company in terms of revenue; after Comcast.)

Chicago Fire is an American television drama series that airs on NBC. The show explores the lives; both professional and personal; of the firefighters and paramedics of the Chicago Fire Department. NBC renewed the series for a third season.)

The Eiffel Tower is an iron lattice tower located on the Champ de Mars in Paris. It was initially criticised by some of France leading artists and intellectuals for its design; but has become both a global cultural icon of France and one of the most recognizable structure in the world.)

Angry Birds is a video game franchise inspired primarily by a sketch of stylized wingless birds; with two billion downloads across all platforms. Angry Birds has been praised for its successful combination of addictive gameplay; comical style; and low price.)
